article.description: Isiah Deas had 16 points as La Salle defeated Saint Bonaventure 73-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Deas scores 16, sparks La Salle past St. Bonaventure, 73-65
article.linkText: Deas scores 16, sparks La Salle past St. Bonaventure, 73-65
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Isiah Deas had 16 points as La Salle defeated Saint Bonaventure 73-65 on Saturday. Sherif Kenney had 14 points for La Salle (14-14, 5-11 Atlantic 10 Conference). David Beatty added 11 points. Saul Phiri had 11 points and seven rebounds. Christian Ray had 6 points and 10 rebounds. Kyle Lofton had 17 points and six assists for the Bonnies (18-11, 10-6). Jaren English added 13 points and nine rebounds. Osun Osunniyi had 11 points. La Salle plays UMass at home on Wednesday. Saint Bonaventure plays Saint Joseph's at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
